    {
      "type": 0,
      "content": "# Packages\n1. `discord-html-transcript-api`: Core package, built with Java.\n2. `discord-html-transcript-jda`: JDA Wrapper\n3. `discord-html-transcript-discordjs`: Discord.js Wrapper\n4. `discord-html-transcript-discordpy`: Discord.py Wrapper\n## 1. discord-html-transcriber\n### Content\n- Includes a JSON schema that's required to generate the HTML using JTE.\n### Flow\nBuilt into a native image using GraalVM that's downloaded by the wrappers.\nWhen ran, it offers an API endpoint locally to accept a payload (Messages) from the wrapper.\n## 2. discord-html-transcriber-js\n### Content\n- Includes a JSON schema (DTO) to match `discord-html-transcriber`'s schema.\n### Flow\nDownloads the `discord-html-transcriber` respective to the OS, runs it locally.\nRetrieves the Messages using Discord.js, passes it to `discord-html-transcriber`'s local server to generate the HTML.",
